Metkore Alloys & Industries LimitedThe Company is engaged in manufacture of high carbon ferro-chrome for use in the stainless steel industry. The installed capacity is 30,000 MT with each 6 MVA and 9 MVA furnace. The Company manufactures two standard grade of ferro chrome i.e. high silicon and low silicon.


Factsheet




Basic InformationNature of BusinessManufacturerAdditional BusinessSupplierLegal Status of FirmPrivate Limited Company









Board of DirectorsMr. Prashant Boorugu Managing Director of the company and looks after strategic management and operations.He hails from a business family of Hyderabad. He is expanding the operationsof MAIL in ferro alloys and has also undertaken backward integration measures like acquiring mining rights.Mr. NagarajuVice President (Operations) of the company. A graduate in Science with certification in Leadership -he has over 24 years of experience in operation and management of ferro alloy plants in India and abroad viz. Indian Metal and Ferro Alloys (IMFA), Bhutan Ferro Alloys, Rohit Ferro Tech, Jindal Ferro Alloys etc.Adviser:Mr. A.V.L.Narasimham A Metallurgical Engineer from REC, Roukela with over 40 years of vast experience in production and operations of ferro alloy plants. He has worked in major ferro alloy companies like Tata, Facor and has rich expertise in process improvements and cost controls.
 




